The paper deals with models of distributed computation, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves topological conditions and computability theory, which are topics in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of topological conditions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the solvability of tasks in distributed systems, which is a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SY).
